properties.areaDesc: Flaming Gorge; East Sweetwater County; Rock Springs and Green River
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 5 at 11:34AM MST until February 7 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Warning for Sweetwater County Thursday afternoon through
Friday...

...Strong winds aloft and a tight surface pressure gradient will
combine for high winds across Sweetwater County Thursday afternoon
through Friday...

* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts of 60 to 65 mph expected.

* WHERE...Rock Springs and Green River, Flaming Gorge and East
Sweetwater County.

* WHEN...From noon Thursday to 5 PM MST Friday. the strongest
winds will blow Thursday afternoon and during the day Friday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation, especially along Interstate
80. An enhanced blow over risk for light and high profile
vehicles including camper trailers and semi trucks.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Some blowing snow may reduce visibility at
times and create slick road surfaces.
properties.instruction:
Use caution if traveling. Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust. In a parking lot,
park into the wind to minimize the possibility of your car door
hitting another parked vehicle.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM NOON THURSDAY TO 5 PM MST FRIDAY
